        <abstract> 
<p>Second <hi rend="italic">Living Cirripedia</hi> volume published. Asks THH’s advice on presentation copies for continental naturalists.</p>  
<p>THH’s review of <hi rend="italic">Vestiges of creation</hi> in [<hi rend="italic">Br. &amp; Foreign Med.-Chir. Rev.</hi> 13 (1854)]. CD is almost as unorthodox on species as the author of <hi rend="italic">Vestiges</hi>, but hopes not quite so unphilosophical.</p> 
            <p>Hopes L. Agassiz was sounder on embryological stages than THH thinks.</p>
        </abstract>
